Prime time programming has long been a weaver of dreams for Taiwanese audiences .
But there is a huge difference between today 's society and that of 30 years ago .
If the dreams woven by the serials stay the same , or are even inferior , inevitably the audience will decline .
Given the ever growing pluralization of society in <COREF ID="33" TYPE="IDENT">Taiwan</COREF> , these shows must find new talent , overcome formulaic stories , and halt the decline in audience share .
